    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    Binder
    Base Binder class (extending CardHolder) with common binder functionality.
    BinderType
    Enumerates the different types of binders available in the Trading Card Inventory System.
    Card
    Represents a trading card with a name, rarity, variant, value, and count.
    CardHolder
    Abstract class representing a generic holder of cards (e.g., a binder or deck).
    CardRarity
    Represents the rarity levels of a trading card.
    CardVariant
    Represents the variants of a trading card.
    CollectorBinder
    A specialized binder for collector-grade cards that only accepts rare/legendary cards with special variants.
    Deck
    Represents a deck of cards in the Trading Card Inventory System.
    DeckType
    Represents the types of decks available.
    LuxuryBinder
    A premium binder for high-value cards with customizable pricing.
    Main
     
    NonCuratedBinder
    Binder that accepts all card types without restrictions.
    NormalDeck
    Normal deck (non-sellable)
    PauperBinder
    Sellable binder for common/uncommon cards only.
    RaresBinder
    Sellable binder for rare and legendary cards with 10% premium.
    Sellable
    Interface for objects that have a monetary value.
    SellableBinder
    Abstract base class for sellable binders that implements the Sellable interface.
    SellableDeck
    Sellable deck (can be sold for its card value)
    TradingCardInventorySystemController
    Controller class for the Trading Card Inventory System.
    TradingCardInventorySystemModel
    The model component of the Trading Card Inventory System.
    TradingCardInventorySystemView
    The view component of the Trading Card Inventory System.
